Gareth Bale has nothing to prove to Wales, according to his international manager Chris Coleman. 

The world's most expensive player has come in for sustained criticism during his second season at Real Madrid, but Coleman said: 'I think I'd be on dangerous ground if I said to Baley: 'I need a bit more from you.'' 

Coleman spoke after naming his squad featuring Bale, Aaron Ramsey, Joe Allen and Ashley Williams. Sam Vokes was also called up for the first time in 12 months following his serious knee injury.

