'He's got no points to prove to us. His fight in Madrid and what he has to prove every time he goes on the pitch is separate from us.' 

Coleman said Bale was 'caught in the middle' at Real but 'will come through'.

'People say he's had a bad season but Real are in the quarter finals of the Champions League, still with a chance of La Liga, and he has scored 16 goals and god knows how many assists. I have no worries about him, he's the last person I'm worried about.' 

